     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="5"/>
   <head>In laudem Authoris.</head>
   <l>THy tun (deare friend) of wit &amp; hony nows brok vp,</l>
   <l>Too long frō men of Art &amp; iudgemēt, though lockt vp,</l>
   <l>For men of Art doe say, it tastes right sweete,</l>
   <l>And men of iudgements, say it is right sound,</l>
   <l>And both a treasure, say of light is found,</l>
   <l>A treasure sure that in extreames will steed.</l>
   <l>And raise thee (haue but patience) from all need,</l>
   <l>O pittie it is such guifts and lights of minde</l>
   <l>Should be obscurde, and die as men doe blinde.</l>
   <l>Some Scipio (or some Caesar) shade thy hiue,</l>
   <l>That thou in spight of Waspes and Flyes maist thriue.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>I.S. Gent.</signed>
   </closer>
